==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Synergism
<hw>Syn"er*gism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Synergetic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>The doctrine or
theory, attributed to Melanchthon, that in the regeneration of a human
soul there is a cooperation, or joint agency, on the part both of God
and of man.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- 2. Same as synergy, 2. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Synergist</ent>⟦br⟧
